{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1041,"text":"TED has already persuaded me\nto change my life in one small way,"},{"time":5395,"text":"by persuading me to change\nthe opening of my speech."},{"time":8766,"text":"I love this idea of engagement."},{"time":11865,"text":"So, when you leave here today,"},{"time":14097,"text":"I'm going to ask you\nto engage or re-engage"},{"time":18047,"text":"with some of the most important\npeople in your lives:"},{"time":20833,"text":"your brothers and sisters."},{"time":22879,"text":"It can be a profoundly\nlife-affirming thing to do,"},{"time":26922,"text":"even if it isn't always easy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":29938,"text":"This is a man named Elliot,"},{"time":32435,"text":"for whom things were very difficult."},{"time":35411,"text":"Elliot was a drunk."},{"time":37175,"text":"He spent most of his life\nbattling alcoholism,"},{"time":41173,"text":"depression, morphine addiction,"},{"time":43792,"text":"and that life ended\nwhen he was just 34 years old."},{"time":47806,"text":"What made things harder for Elliot\nis that his last name was Roosevelt."},{"time":52253,"text":"And he could never quite\nget past the comparisons"},{"time":55136,"text":"with his big brother Teddy,"},{"time":56875,"text":"for whom things always seemed\nto come a little bit easier."}]},{"cues":[{"time":61083,"text":"It wasn't easy being Bobby, either."},{"time":63707,"text":"He was also the sibling of a president."},{"time":65952,"text":"But he adored his brother, Jack."},{"time":68327,"text":"He fought for him,"},{"time":69811,"text":"he worked for him."},{"time":71395,"text":"And when Jack died, he bled for him, too."},{"time":75244,"text":"In the years that followed,\nBobby would smile,"},{"time":78723,"text":"but it seemed labored."},{"time":80378,"text":"He'd lose himself in his work,"},{"time":82509,"text":"but it seemed tortured."},{"time":84493,"text":"Bobby's own death, so similar to John's,"},{"time":88218,"text":"seems somehow fitting."},{"time":90337,"text":"John Kennedy was robbed of his young life;"},{"time":93548,"text":"Bobby seemed almost\nto have been relieved of his."}]},{"cues":[{"time":98324,"text":"There may be no relationship\nthat effects us more profoundly,"},{"time":102855,"text":"that's closer, finer, harder,"},{"time":106223,"text":"sweeter, happier, sadder,"},{"time":109371,"text":"more filled with joy or fraught with woe"},{"time":112373,"text":"than the relationship we have\nwith our brothers and sisters."},{"time":116114,"text":"There's power in the sibling bond."},{"time":120174,"text":"There's pageantry."},{"time":123220,"text":"There's petulance, too,"},{"time":124938,"text":"as when Neil Bush,"},{"time":127405,"text":"sibling of both a president\nand a governor, famously griped,"},{"time":131338,"text":"\"I've lost patience for being compared\nto my older brothers,\""},{"time":136484,"text":"as if Jeb and George W\nwere somehow responsible"},{"time":140315,"text":"for the savings and loan scandal\nand the messy divorce"},{"time":143203,"text":"that marked Neil in the public eye."}]},{"cues":[{"time":147264,"text":"But more important\nthan all of these things,"},{"time":149974,"text":"the sibling bond can be\na thing of abiding love."},{"time":153219,"text":"Our parents leave us too early,"},{"time":155635,"text":"our spouse and our children\ncome along too late."},{"time":159036,"text":"Our siblings are the only ones\nwho are with us"},{"time":162098,"text":"for the entire ride."},{"time":164280,"text":"Over the arc of decades,\nthere may be nothing"},{"time":166951,"text":"that defines us and forms us\nmore powerfully"},{"time":170500,"text":"than our relationship\nwith our sisters and brothers."},{"time":173723,"text":"It was true for me,"},{"time":175731,"text":"it's true for your children"},{"time":177809,"text":"and if you have siblings,\nit's true for you, too."}]},{"cues":[{"time":181227,"text":"This picture was taken when Steve,\non the left, was eight years old."},{"time":185193,"text":"I was six, our brother Gary was five\nand my brother Bruce was four."},{"time":190176,"text":"I will not say what year it was taken."},{"time":192350,"text":"It was not this year."}]},{"cues":[{"time":193967,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":195308,"text":"I open my new book, \"The Sibling Effect,\""},{"time":198091,"text":"on a Saturday morning,"},{"time":199579,"text":"not long before this picture was taken,"},{"time":201991,"text":"when the three older brothers decided\nthat it might be a very good idea"},{"time":205735,"text":"to lock the younger brother\nin a fuse cabinet in our playroom."}]},{"cues":[{"time":209242,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":210400,"text":"We were, believe it or not,\ntrying to keep him safe."}]},{"cues":[{"time":215195,"text":"Our father was a hotheaded man,"},{"time":218158,"text":"somebody who didn't take kindly\nto being disturbed on Saturday mornings."},{"time":222823,"text":"I don't know what he thought his life\nwould be like on Saturday mornings"},{"time":226362,"text":"when he had four sons,"},{"time":227541,"text":"ages four years old or younger\nwhen the youngest one was born,"},{"time":230610,"text":"but they weren't quiet."},{"time":232272,"text":"He did not take to that well."},{"time":234488,"text":"And he would react to being\ndisturbed on a Saturday morning"},{"time":238087,"text":"by stalking into the playroom"},{"time":239997,"text":"and administering a very freewheeling\nform of a corporal punishment,"},{"time":243933,"text":"lashing out at whoever\nwas within arms' reach."},{"time":247938,"text":"We were by no means battered children\nbut we did get hit,"},{"time":251514,"text":"and we found it terrifying."}]},{"cues":[{"time":253784,"text":"So we devised a sort of\nscatter-and-hide drill."}]},{"cues":[{"time":256778,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":257837,"text":"As soon as we saw or heard\nthe footsteps coming,"},{"time":261763,"text":"Steve, the oldest, would wriggle\nunder the couch,"},{"time":264756,"text":"I would dive into the closet\nin the playroom,"},{"time":268424,"text":"Gary would dive into\na window-seat toy chest,"},{"time":271363,"text":"but not before we closed\nBruce inside the fuse box."},{"time":274912,"text":"We told him it was\nAlan Shepard's space capsule,"},{"time":277783,"text":"and that somehow made it work better."}]},{"cues":[{"time":279570,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":281735,"text":"I dare say my father was never\nfooled by this ruse."},{"time":285472,"text":"And it was only in later\nyears that I began to think"},{"time":288218,"text":"perhaps it wasn't a good idea\nto squeeze a four-year-old"},{"time":291207,"text":"up against a panel of old-style,\nun-screwable high-voltage fuses."}]},{"cues":[{"time":296299,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":297762,"text":"But my brothers and I,\neven through those unhappy times,"},{"time":302261,"text":"came through them, with something\nthat was clear and hard and fine:"},{"time":307584,"text":"a primal appreciation\nfor the bond we shared."},{"time":311639,"text":"We were a unit -- a loud, messy"},{"time":315380,"text":"brawling, loyal, loving,"},{"time":318219,"text":"lasting unit."},{"time":320400,"text":"We felt much stronger that way\nthan we ever could as individuals."},{"time":324824,"text":"And we knew that as our lives went on,"},{"time":327325,"text":"we could always be able\nto call on that strength."}]},{"cues":[{"time":331299,"text":"We're not alone."},{"time":332706,"text":"Until 15 years ago,"},{"time":334508,"text":"scientists didn't really pay much\nattention to the sibling bond."},{"time":337886,"text":"And with good reason:"},{"time":339149,"text":"you have just one mother,\nyou have just one father"},{"time":342299,"text":"if you do marriage right,\nyou have one spouse for life."},{"time":345623,"text":"Siblings can claim\nnone of that uniqueness."},{"time":348225,"text":"They're interchangeable, fungible,\na kind of household commodity."},{"time":352634,"text":"Parents set up shop and begin stocking\ntheir shelves with inventory,"},{"time":356919,"text":"the only limitation being sperm,\negg and economics."}]},{"cues":[{"time":359980,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":361011,"text":"As long as you can keep breathing,\nyou may as well keep stocking."},{"time":364432,"text":"Now, nature is perfectly happy\nwith that arrangement,"},{"time":368136,"text":"because our primal directive here"},{"time":370848,"text":"is to get as many of our genes\nas possible into the next generation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":375581,"text":"Animals wrestle with\nthese same issues, too,"},{"time":378401,"text":"but they have a more straightforward way\nof dealing with things."},{"time":381853,"text":"A crested penguin that has laid two eggs\nwill take a good look at them"},{"time":385564,"text":"and boot the smaller one out of the nest,"},{"time":388223,"text":"the better to focus her attentions\non the presumably heartier chick"},{"time":391909,"text":"in the bigger shell."},{"time":394366,"text":"A black eagle will allow\nall of her chicks to hatch"},{"time":397648,"text":"and then stand back while the bigger ones\nfight it out with the little ones,"},{"time":401599,"text":"typically ripping them to ribbons"},{"time":403294,"text":"and then settling back\nto grow up in peace."},{"time":406587,"text":"Piglets, cute as they are,"},{"time":408715,"text":"are born with a strange\nlittle outward set of pointing teeth,"},{"time":412844,"text":"that they use to jab at one another"},{"time":414755,"text":"as they compete\nfor the choicest nursing spots."}]},{"cues":[{"time":419685,"text":"The problem for scientists"},{"time":421892,"text":"was that this whole idea of siblings\nas second-class citizens"},{"time":426797,"text":"never really seemed to hold up."},{"time":430046,"text":"After the researchers\nhad learned all they could"},{"time":433696,"text":"from the relationships in the family,\nmothers and other relationships,"},{"time":439640,"text":"they still came up with some\ntemperamental dark matter"},{"time":442875,"text":"that was pulling at us,"},{"time":444242,"text":"exerting a gravity all its own."},{"time":446421,"text":"And that could only be our siblings."}]},{"cues":[{"time":449806,"text":"Humans are no different from animals."},{"time":453842,"text":"After we are born, we do whatever we can"},{"time":458142,"text":"to attract the attention of our parents,"},{"time":460240,"text":"determining what our strongest\nselling points are"},{"time":463460,"text":"and marketing them ferociously."},{"time":465775,"text":"Someone's the funny one,\nsomeone's the pretty one,"},{"time":468355,"text":"someone's the athlete,\nsomeone's the smart one."},{"time":473625,"text":"Scientists call this \"deidentification.\""},{"time":476588,"text":"If my older brother\nis a high-school football player --"},{"time":479279,"text":"which, if you saw my older\nbrother, you'd know he was not --"},{"time":482214,"text":"I could become a high-school\nfootball player, too"},{"time":484788,"text":"and get at most 50 percent of the applause\nin my family for doing that."},{"time":490399,"text":"Or, I could become student\ncouncil president"},{"time":493940,"text":"or specialize in the arts"},{"time":495935,"text":"and get 100 percent\nof the attention in that area."}]},{"cues":[{"time":499917,"text":"Sometimes parents contaminate\nthe deidentification process,"},{"time":503803,"text":"communicating to their kids subtly or not,"},{"time":506474,"text":"that only certain kinds of accomplishments\nwill be applauded in the home."},{"time":511556,"text":"Joe Kennedy was famous for this,"},{"time":514104,"text":"making it clear to his nine children"},{"time":516282,"text":"that they were expected to compete\nwith one another in athletics"},{"time":519480,"text":"and were expected to win,"},{"time":521755,"text":"lest they be made to eat\nin the kitchen with the help,"},{"time":524989,"text":"rather than in the dining room\nwith the family."},{"time":528934,"text":"It's no wonder"},{"time":530135,"text":"that scrawny second-born Jack Kennedy\nfought so hard to compete"},{"time":534817,"text":"with his fitter firstborn brother, Joe,"},{"time":537236,"text":"often at his peril,"},{"time":538802,"text":"at one point, engaging\nin a bicycle race around the house"},{"time":542275,"text":"that resulted in a collision\ncosting John 28 stitches."},{"time":546663,"text":"Joe walked away essentially unharmed."}]},{"cues":[{"time":550134,"text":"Parents exacerbate this problem further"},{"time":553073,"text":"when they exhibit favoritism,"},{"time":555669,"text":"which they do overwhelmingly,\nno matter how much they admit it."},{"time":560207,"text":"A study I cite in this TIME magazine\ncovering in the book \"The Sibling Effect,\""},{"time":564800,"text":"found 70 percent of fathers\nand 65 percent of mothers"},{"time":569755,"text":"exhibit a preference\nfor at least one child."},{"time":572958,"text":"And keep in mind here --\nthe keyword is \"exhibit.\""},{"time":576854,"text":"The remaining parents may simply be doing\na better job of concealing things."}]},{"cues":[{"time":581341,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":583231,"text":"I like to say that 95 percent\nof all parents have a favorite,"},{"time":588795,"text":"five percent are lying about it."},{"time":591178,"text":"The exception is my wife and me."},{"time":593093,"text":"Honestly, we do not have a favorite."}]},{"cues":[{"time":595788,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":597893,"text":"It's not parents' fault that they harbor\nfeelings of favoritism."},{"time":601497,"text":"And here, too, our natural\nwiring is at work."},{"time":605116,"text":"Firstborns are the first products\non the familial assembly line."},{"time":609767,"text":"Parents typically get two years\nof investing dollars, calories"},{"time":614740,"text":"and so many other resources in them,"},{"time":617094,"text":"so that by the time\nthe second born comes along,"},{"time":620186,"text":"the firstborn is already ...\nit's what corporations call \"sunk costs,\""},{"time":624483,"text":"you don't want to disinvest in this one"},{"time":626908,"text":"and launch the R&amp;D on the new product."}]},{"cues":[{"time":628954,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":630041,"text":"So what we begin to do is say,\n\"I'm going to lean to the Mac OS X"},{"time":635141,"text":"and let the Mac OS XI come out\nin a couple of years.\""},{"time":638032,"text":"So we tend to lean in that direction."}]},{"cues":[{"time":639918,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":641074,"text":"But there are other forces at work, too."},{"time":643483,"text":"One of the same studies I looked at\nboth here and in the book found that,"},{"time":648746,"text":"improbably, the most common favorite\nfor a father is the last-born daughter."},{"time":655646,"text":"The most common favorite\nfor a mother is the firstborn son."},{"time":659540,"text":"Now, this isn't Oedipal; never mind\nwhat the Freudians would have told us"},{"time":663166,"text":"a hundred years ago."},{"time":664349,"text":"And it's not just that fathers\nare habitually wrapped around"},{"time":667249,"text":"the fingers of their little girls,"},{"time":668922,"text":"though I can tell you that,\nas the father of two girls,"},{"time":671605,"text":"that part definitely plays a role."},{"time":674735,"text":"Rather, there is a certain\nreproductive narcissism at work."},{"time":678770,"text":"Your opposite-gender kids"},{"time":683606,"text":"can never resemble you exactly."},{"time":687343,"text":"But if somehow they can resemble\nyou temperamentally,"},{"time":690751,"text":"you'll love them all the more."},{"time":692487,"text":"As the result, the father\nwho is a businessman will just melt"},{"time":697534,"text":"at the idea of his MBA daughter\nwith a tough-as-nails worldview."},{"time":703191,"text":"The mother who is a sensitive type\nwill go gooey over her son the poet."}]},{"cues":[{"time":707332,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":709250,"text":"Birth order, another topic\nI covered for TIME,"},{"time":712635,"text":"and another topic I cover in the book,"},{"time":716434,"text":"plays out in other ways as well."},{"time":718461,"text":"Long before scientists\nbegan looking at this,"},{"time":721664,"text":"parents noticed that there are\ncertain temperamental templates"},{"time":725138,"text":"associated with all birth rankings:"},{"time":727361,"text":"the serious, striving firstborn;"},{"time":730302,"text":"the caught-in-a-thicket's middle born;"},{"time":732683,"text":"the wild child of a last born."},{"time":735309,"text":"And once again, when science\ndid crack this field,"},{"time":737954,"text":"they found out mom and dad are right."}]},{"cues":[{"time":740322,"text":"Firstborns across history have tended\nto be bigger and healthier"},{"time":744745,"text":"than later borns,"},{"time":746039,"text":"in part, because of the head start\nthey got on food"},{"time":748569,"text":"in an area in which it could be scarce."},{"time":751018,"text":"Firstborns are also\nvaccinated more reliably"},{"time":754597,"text":"and tend to have more\nfollow-up visits to doctors"},{"time":758116,"text":"when they get sick."},{"time":759412,"text":"And this pattern continues today."},{"time":761563,"text":"This IQ question is, sadly -- I can\nsay this as a second-born --"},{"time":765591,"text":"a very real thing."},{"time":767304,"text":"Firstborns have a three-point\nIQ advantage over second borns"},{"time":771077,"text":"and second borns have a 1.5 IQ\nadvantage over later borns,"},{"time":775030,"text":"partly because of the exclusive attention\nfirstborns get from mom and dad,"},{"time":779513,"text":"and partly because they get a chance\nto mentor the younger kids."},{"time":784202,"text":"All of this explains why firstborns\nare likelier to be CEOs,"},{"time":788166,"text":"they are likelier to be senators,"},{"time":789822,"text":"they are likelier to be astronauts,"},{"time":791639,"text":"and they are likelier to earn more\nthan other kids are."}]},{"cues":[{"time":795936,"text":"Last borns come into the world\nwith a whole different set of challenges."},{"time":800529,"text":"The smallest and weakest cubs in the den,"},{"time":803212,"text":"they're at the greatest risk\nof getting eaten alive,"},{"time":806296,"text":"so they have to develop\nwhat are called \"low-power skills\" --"},{"time":809573,"text":"the ability to charm and disarm,"},{"time":812001,"text":"to intuit what's going on\nin someone else's head,"},{"time":814930,"text":"the better to duck\nthe punch before it lands."}]},{"cues":[{"time":817549,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":818946,"text":"They're also flat-out funnier,"},{"time":821627,"text":"which is another thing\nthat comes in handy,"},{"time":823874,"text":"because a person who's making you laugh\nis a very hard person to slug."}]},{"cues":[{"time":827826,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":829006,"text":"It's perhaps no coincidence\nthat over the course of history,"},{"time":832904,"text":"some of our greatest satirists --"},{"time":834969,"text":"Swift,"},{"time":836621,"text":"Twain,"},{"time":838396,"text":"Voltaire,"},{"time":840592,"text":"Colbert --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":841819,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":843930,"text":"are either the last borns"},{"time":845817,"text":"or among the last in very large families."}]},{"cues":[{"time":849657,"text":"Most middle borns don't get\nquite as sweet a deal."},{"time":852465,"text":"I think of us as the flyover states."},{"time":854707,"text":"We are --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":856380,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":859184,"text":"we're the ones who fight harder\nfor recognition in the home."},{"time":863033,"text":"We're the ones who are always\nraising our hands"},{"time":866141,"text":"while someone else at the table\nis getting called on."},{"time":869170,"text":"We're the ones who tend\nto take a little longer"},{"time":871830,"text":"to find their direction in life."},{"time":874052,"text":"And there can be self-esteem\nissues associated with that,"},{"time":877484,"text":"notwithstanding the fact\nthat I've been asked to do TED,"},{"time":880209,"text":"so I feel much better\nabout these things right now."}]},{"cues":[{"time":882726,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":883753,"text":"But the upside for middle borns\nis that they also tend to develop"},{"time":888514,"text":"denser and richer relationships\noutside the home."},{"time":892142,"text":"But that advantage comes also\nfrom something of a disadvantage,"},{"time":895407,"text":"simply because their needs\nweren't met as well in the home."}]},{"cues":[{"time":899751,"text":"The feuds in the playroom\nthat play out over favoritism,"},{"time":903184,"text":"birth order and so many other issues"},{"time":905783,"text":"are as unrelenting as they seem."},{"time":908115,"text":"In one study I cite in the book,"},{"time":910600,"text":"children in the two-to-four age group"},{"time":913426,"text":"engage in one fight every 6.3 minutes,"},{"time":919026,"text":"or 9.5 fights an hour."},{"time":922326,"text":"That's not fighting --\nthat's performance art."}]},{"cues":[{"time":925074,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":926126,"text":"That's extraordinary."}]},{"cues":[{"time":928939,"text":"One reason for this is that there are\na lot more people in your home"},{"time":932873,"text":"than you think there are,"},{"time":934258,"text":"or at least a lot more relationships."},{"time":936775,"text":"Every person in your house has\na discrete one-on-one relationship"},{"time":941081,"text":"with every other person,"},{"time":942485,"text":"and those pairings or dyads add up fast."},{"time":946344,"text":"In a family with two parents and two kids,\nthere are six dyads:"},{"time":951532,"text":"Mom has a relationship with child A and B,"},{"time":954215,"text":"Dad has a relationship with child A and B."},{"time":957041,"text":"There's the marital relationship,"},{"time":958836,"text":"and there is the relationship\nbetween the kids themselves."},{"time":962208,"text":"The formula for this\nlooks very chilly but it's real."},{"time":965703,"text":"K equals the number of people\nin your household,"},{"time":970596,"text":"and X equals the number of dyads."},{"time":974567,"text":"In a five-person family,\nthere are ten discrete dyads."},{"time":978743,"text":"The eight-person Brady Bunch --\nnever mind the sweetness here --"},{"time":982003,"text":"there were 28 dyads in that family."},{"time":985319,"text":"The original Kennedy family with nine kids\nhad 55 different relationships."},{"time":990921,"text":"And Bobby Kennedy, who grew up\nto have 11 children of his own,"},{"time":994857,"text":"had a household with a whopping 91 dyads."},{"time":999133,"text":"This overpopulation of relationships"},{"time":1003493,"text":"makes fights unavoidable."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1006079,"text":"And far and away the biggest trigger\nfor all sibling fights is property."},{"time":1011617,"text":"Studies have found that over 95 percent\nof the fights among small children"},{"time":1016804,"text":"concern somebody touching, playing with,"},{"time":1019846,"text":"looking at the other person's stuff."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1022698,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1023725,"text":"This in its own way is healthy\nif it's very noisy,"},{"time":1028474,"text":"and the reason is that small children\ncome into the world"},{"time":1032391,"text":"with absolutely no control."},{"time":1034335,"text":"They are utterly helpless."},{"time":1036045,"text":"The only way they have\nof projecting their very limited power"},{"time":1040740,"text":"is through the objects\nthey can call their own."},{"time":1043372,"text":"When somebody crosses\nthat very erasable line,"},{"time":1046992,"text":"they're going to go nuts,\nand that's what happens."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1050762,"text":"Another very common casus belli\namong children is the idea of fairness,"},{"time":1056401,"text":"as any parent who hears 14 times a day,\n\"But that's unfair!\""},{"time":1061031,"text":"can tell you."},{"time":1062569,"text":"In a way this is good, too, though."},{"time":1065031,"text":"Kids are born with a very innate sense\nof right and wrong,"},{"time":1068859,"text":"of a fair deal versus an unfair one,"},{"time":1071567,"text":"and this teaches them powerful lessons."},{"time":1073846,"text":"Do you want to know how powerfully encoded\nfairness is in the human genome?"},{"time":1078959,"text":"We process that phenomenon"},{"time":1081581,"text":"through the same lobe in our brain\nthat processes disgust,"},{"time":1085781,"text":"meaning we react to the idea\nof somebody being cheated"},{"time":1090567,"text":"the same way we react to putrefied meat."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1093514,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1094711,"text":"Any wonder that this fellow,\nBernie Madoff, is unpopular?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1102047,"text":"All of these dramas played out day to day,"},{"time":1105306,"text":"moment to moment,"},{"time":1106835,"text":"serve as a real-time,\ntotal-immersion exercise for life."},{"time":1112045,"text":"Siblings teach each other conflict\navoidance and conflict resolution,"},{"time":1116909,"text":"when to stand up for themselves,"},{"time":1119329,"text":"when to stand down;"},{"time":1120969,"text":"they learn love,"},{"time":1122625,"text":"loyalty, honesty, sharing,\ncaring, compromise,"},{"time":1128245,"text":"the disclosure of secrets\nand much more important,"},{"time":1131644,"text":"the keeping of confidences."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1135481,"text":"I listen to my young daughters --\naren’t they adorable? --"},{"time":1138354,"text":"I listen to my young daughters\ntalking late into the night,"},{"time":1142741,"text":"the same way my parents, no doubt,\nlistened to my brothers and me talking,"},{"time":1146836,"text":"and sometimes I intervene,\nbut usually I don't."},{"time":1150747,"text":"They're part of a conversation\nI am not part of,"},{"time":1154148,"text":"nobody else in the world is part of,"},{"time":1156241,"text":"and it's a conversation\nthat can and should go on"},{"time":1159857,"text":"for the rest of their lives."},{"time":1161751,"text":"From this will come a sense of constancy,"},{"time":1164553,"text":"a sense of having a permanent\ntraveling companion,"},{"time":1167679,"text":"somebody with whom they road-tested life"},{"time":1170376,"text":"before they ever had to get out\nand travel it on their own."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1174550,"text":"Brothers and sisters aren't\nthe sine qua non of a happy life;"},{"time":1178393,"text":"plenty of adult sibling\nrelationships are fatally broken"},{"time":1181599,"text":"and need to be abandoned\nfor the sanity of everybody involved."},{"time":1185518,"text":"And only-children, throughout history,\nhave shown themselves"},{"time":1189886,"text":"to be creatively, brilliantly capable"},{"time":1192705,"text":"of getting their socialization\nand comradeship skills"},{"time":1196117,"text":"through friends, through cousins,\nthrough classmates."},{"time":1200080,"text":"But having siblings and not\nmaking the most of those bonds"},{"time":1204197,"text":"is, I believe, folly of the first order."},{"time":1207670,"text":"If relationships are broken\nand are fixable, fix them."},{"time":1212276,"text":"If they work, make them even better."},{"time":1214996,"text":"Failing to do so is a little like having\na thousand acres of fertile farmland"},{"time":1220190,"text":"and never planting it."},{"time":1221897,"text":"Yes, you can always get your food\nat the supermarket,"},{"time":1226017,"text":"but think what you're\nallowing to lie fallow."},{"time":1229284,"text":"Life is short, it's finite,\nand it plays for keeps."},{"time":1234486,"text":"Siblings may be among the richest harvests\nof the time we have here."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1239520,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1240697,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}